<title>FINLAND: UPM CEO calm on markka-ERM link.</title>
<headline>UPM CEO calm on markka-ERM link.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1996-10-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Juha Niemela, CEO of Europe's biggest forestry group UPM-Kymmene Oy, said Finnish forest industry will be unfazed by the government's move to link the markka to the ERM.</p>
<p>&quot;Forest companies as well as other export companies have already during recent years faced a new situation. In practice, we have not had an opportunity to devalue any more, and we will not have,&quot; Niemela said in a radio interview.</p>
<p>The link rate of 5.80 markka per ECU announced on Saturday was &quot;moderate&quot; for the forest industry, Niemela said.</p>
<p>&quot;When determining it, export industry's hopes were taken into consideration reasonably well. It is the recent moderate markka-rate, I will not criticize it,&quot; Niemela said.</p>
<p>&quot;Now we just have to control our costs and to live like our biggest competitors,&quot; he said, and referred to Swedish and German forest companies.</p>
<p>-- Helsinki newsroom +358-0-6805 0248</p>
